# {{project_name}}

A crowdfunding escrow contract (funding target + deadline), generated by
[soroban-forge](https://github.com/soroban-forge-labs/soroban-forge) from the
`crowdfund` template.

## How it works

1. The contract is deployed with an `owner`, a pledge `token`, a `target`
   amount and a `deadline` (unix timestamp).
2. Backers call `pledge(from, amount)` before the deadline; tokens are held in
   escrow by the contract.
3. After the deadline:
   - target reached → `claim()` sends all funds to the owner (once);
   - target missed → `refund(to)` returns each backer's pledge.

## Develop

```sh
cargo test
stellar contract build
```

## Deploy to testnet

```sh
stellar contract deploy \
  --wasm target/wasm32v1-none/release/{{crate_name}}.wasm \
  --source-account <your-identity> \
  --network testnet \
  -- --owner <OWNER_ADDRESS> --token <TOKEN_ADDRESS> --target 10000000 --deadline 1790000000
```
